# Tailwind to SCSS Module Conversion Guide

BEM naming, units (px), and property sorting: see **scss-module-standards.mdc**. This rule covers conversion steps and Tailwind→SCSS mapping only.

## Overview
This rule provides a systematic approach for converting existing Tailwind CSS classes to SCSS modules, ensuring consistency and maintainability across the codebase.

## Conversion Process

### Step 1: Analyze Existing Tailwind Classes
Before conversion, identify all Tailwind classes in the component:
- Layout classes (`flex`, `grid`, `absolute`, etc.)
- Sizing classes (`w-4`, `h-4`, `max-w-[350px]`, etc.)
- Spacing classes (`p-4`, `m-2`, `gap-4`, etc.)
- Color classes (`bg-c24-fusion-blue`, `fill-c24-yellow`, etc.)
- Typography classes (`text-xs`, `font-bold`, etc.)
- State classes (`hover:`, `focus:`, etc.)

### Step 2: Create SCSS Module Structure
```scss
.ComponentName {
  // Main component styles
  
  &_element {
    // Element-specific styles
  }
  
  &_anotherElement {
    // Another element styles
  }
  
  &___modifier {
    // Modifier styles (triple underscore)
  }
}
```

### Step 3: Convert Common Tailwind Patterns

#### Flexbox Layouts
```scss
// Tailwind: flex items-center justify-between
.Component_container {
  align-items: center;
  display: flex;
  justify-content: space-between;
}

// Tailwind: flex flex-col gap-4
.Component_column {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 16px;
}

// Tailwind: flex-wrap
.Component_wrap {
  display: flex;
  flex-wrap: wrap;
}
```

#### Positioning
```scss
// Tailwind: absolute top-4 right-0
.Component_positioned {
  position: absolute;
  right: 0;
  top: 16px;
}

// Tailwind: relative z-10
.Component_layered {
  position: relative;
  z-index: 10;
}

// Tailwind: sticky top-0
.Component_sticky {
  position: sticky;
  top: 0;
}
```

#### Sizing and Spacing
```scss
// Tailwind: w-full h-full
.Component_fullSize {
  height: 100%;
  width: 100%;
}

// Tailwind: !w-4 !h-4 (important for overrides)
.Component_icon {
  height: 16px !important;
  width: 16px !important;
}

// Tailwind: p-4 pr-8
.Component_padded {
  padding: 16px 32px 16px 16px;
}

// Tailwind: mt-[-1px] (negative margins)
.Component_negativeMargin {
  margin-top: -1px;
}
```

#### Colors and Backgrounds
```scss
// Tailwind: bg-c24-fusion-blue
.Component_background {
  background-color: var(--c24-color-fusion-blue);
}

// Tailwind: fill-c24-yellow
.Component_stars {
  fill: var(--c24-color-yellow);
}

// Tailwind: text-c24-grey
.Component_greyText {
  color: var(--c24-color-grey);
}

// Tailwind: border-t border-t-c24-light-grey
.Component_topBorder {
  border-top: 1px solid var(--c24-color-light-grey);
}
```

#### Typography
```scss
// Tailwind: text-xs
.Component_smallText {
  font-size: 12px;
}

// Tailwind: font-bold
.Component_boldText {
  font-weight: bold;
}

// Tailwind: whitespace-nowrap
.Component_noWrap {
  white-space: nowrap;
}
```

#### Special Cases
```scss
// Tailwind: rounded-full
.Component_circular {
  border-radius: 50%;
}

// Tailwind: overflow-hidden
.Component_clipped {
  overflow: hidden;
}

// Tailwind: cursor-pointer
.Component_clickable {
  cursor: pointer;
}

// Tailwind: rotate-90
.Component_rotated {
  transform: rotate(90deg);
}
```

## Unit Conversion Reference

### Rem to Pixel Conversion
- `0.25rem` → `4px`
- `0.5rem` → `8px`
- `0.75rem` → `12px`
- `1rem` → `16px`
- `1.25rem` → `20px`
- `1.5rem` → `24px`
- `2rem` → `32px`
- `2.5rem` → `40px`
- `3rem` → `48px`

### Tailwind Spacing Scale
- `1` → `4px`
- `2` → `8px`
- `3` → `12px`
- `4` → `16px`
- `5` → `20px`
- `6` → `24px`
- `8` → `32px`
- `10` → `40px`
- `12` → `48px`

## Complex Component Conversion Examples

### Multi-Class Element Conversion
```tsx
// Before: Multiple Tailwind classes
<div className="flex items-center justify-between p-4 bg-white border-t border-gray-200">

// After: Single SCSS class
<div className={styles.Component_header}>

// SCSS:
.Component {
  &_header {
    align-items: center;
    background-color: white;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--c24-color-gray-200);
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    padding: 16px;
  }
}
```

### Conditional Classes Conversion
```tsx
// Before: Conditional Tailwind classes
<div className={`flex ${isActive ? 'bg-blue-500' : 'bg-gray-200'} p-4`}>

// After: Conditional SCSS classes
<div className={isActive ? styles.Component_activeContainer : styles.Component_inactiveContainer}>

// SCSS:
.Component {
  &_activeContainer {
    background-color: var(--c24-color-blue-500);
    display: flex;
    padding: 16px;
  }
  
  &_inactiveContainer {
    background-color: var(--c24-color-gray-200);
    display: flex;
    padding: 16px;
  }
}
```

### Important Declarations for Library Overrides
```scss
// When overriding external library styles
.Component {
  &_libraryIcon {
    background-color: var(--c24-color-nobel-grey) !important;
    height: 16px !important;
    width: 16px !important;
  }
  
  &_skeletonElement {
    height: 32px !important;
    width: 220px !important;
  }
}
```

## Semantic Naming Guidelines

### Purpose-Based Naming
```scss
// GOOD - Describes purpose
.Component {
  &_closeButton { /* styles */ }
  &_navigationMenu { /* styles */ }
  &_contentArea { /* styles */ }
  &_userAvatar { /* styles */ }
}

// AVOID - Describes styling
.Component {
  &_redButton { /* styles */ }
  &_flexContainer { /* styles */ }
  &_paddedDiv { /* styles */ }
  &_circularImage { /* styles */ }
}
```

### State-Based Naming
```scss
.Component {
  &_button {
    // Base button styles
  }
  
  &_button___active {
    // Active state styles
  }
  
  &_button___disabled {
    // Disabled state styles
  }
  
  &_button___loading {
    // Loading state styles
  }
}
```

## Testing After Conversion
1. **Visual Regression**: Ensure the component looks identical after conversion
2. **Responsive Behavior**: Test on different screen sizes
3. **Interactive States**: Test hover, focus, and active states
4. **Browser Compatibility**: Test across supported browsers
5. **Performance**: Ensure no performance degradation

## Common Pitfalls to Avoid
- **Forgetting !important**: When overriding library styles
- **Using rem units**: Always use px for consistency
- **Unsorted properties**: Always sort CSS properties alphabetically
- **Style-based naming**: Use semantic names instead
- **Multiple classes**: Combine into single comprehensive classes
- **Missing imports**: Don't forget to import the SCSS module

## Migration Checklist
- [ ] Identify all Tailwind classes in component
- [ ] Create `.module.scss` file with BEM structure
- [ ] Convert all classes using semantic naming
- [ ] Use pixel units and alphabetical sorting
- [ ] Import SCSS module in component
- [ ] Replace className attributes
- [ ] Test visual consistency
- [ ] Update any related tests or stories
